## Description

All API endpoints are currently unprotected from abusive or high-frequency requests. There is no rate limiting middleware configured anywhere in the NestJS application.

This creates two distinct risks:

1. **GitHub API ban risk** — Endpoints like `/api/contributor/contributors` and `/api/contributor/stats/:username` trigger fan-out calls to the GitHub API (N+1 pattern). A single bad actor repeatedly hitting these endpoints can exhaust the GitHub API rate limit (5,000 req/hr for authenticated tokens), causing a **temporary API ban** that breaks the entire application for all users.

2. **DoS risk** — Any endpoint can be flooded at no cost to an attacker, creating availability issues.

## Affected Endpoints

| Endpoint | Risk |
|----------|------|
| `GET /api/contributor/contributors` | Triggers 100+ GitHub calls per request |
| `GET /api/contributor/stats/:username` | 2 GitHub Search API calls per request |
| `GET /api/contributor/issues/:username` | 1+ GitHub Search API calls |
| `GET /api/contributor/pull-requests/:username` | 1+ GitHub Search API calls + N detail fetches |
| `GET /api/projects/projects` | Triggers N+1 PR fetches on cache miss |

## Expected Behavior

Requests exceeding a defined threshold per IP within a time window should receive a `429 Too Many Requests` response, preventing downstream GitHub API abuse.

## Suggested Fix

Install and configure `@nestjs/throttler`:

```bash
npm install @nestjs/throttler
```

Register globally in `app.module.ts`:

```ts
import { ThrottlerModule, ThrottlerGuard } from '@nestjs/throttler';
import { APP_GUARD } from '@nestjs/core';

@Module({
  imports: [
    ThrottlerModule.forRoot([{
      ttl: 60000,   // 1 minute window
      limit: 30,    // max 30 requests per IP per minute
    }]),
    // ...existing modules
  ],
  providers: [
    {
      provide: APP_GUARD,
      useClass: ThrottlerGuard,
    },
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```
